formatTodo distinguishes empty vs clean: if no specs and no markers exist, it returns "Nothing to check: no specs or markers registered." with guidance. If synced, it returns "No changes detected. N specs, M markers, K links, R refs in sync." Otherwise it prints summary counts bucketed by kind (link drift, ref-chain drift, cascade drift, new ref edge(s), removed ref edge(s), broken ref(s)), then lists each todo with a kind-specific format: link-edge todos show marker/spec file locations, drift reason, and reset command; ref-chain and cascade todos show the affected node and the source spec; ref-added/removed/broken todos show the declared ref edge and the appropriate reset command. The todo command exits 0 when clean (all linked + in sync), 1 when drift exists or unlinked markers are present, 2 on error. See principles.friction and unlinked_warning.